Match Day Six of the Nigeria Professional Football League (NPFL) will hold today across various centres in the country. Third-placed team in Group A abridged league, Enyimba Football Club of Aba will host El Kanemi Warriors Football Club of Maiduguri, while Akwa United of Uyo will host Remo Stars Football Club at the Akwa Ibom International Stadium in Uyo. Other clashes are Kwara United Football Club on the road taking on Plateau United at the New Jos Township Stadium, just as Shooting Stars of Ibadan will face Nasarawa FC at the Lekan Salami Stadium, Adamasingba, Ibadan. In Group B, Doma United FC will welcome league leaders, Rivers United, at the Gombe Stadium, while high-flying Lobi Stars will travel to Minna as they face Niger Tornadoes in an away game at the Bako Kontagora Stadium. Other fixtures in the group B will be a tough challenge for the Sunshine Stars of Akure, as they host the Bayelsa United at the Ondo State Sports Complex, while bottom placed, Wikki Tourists will be welcome Enugu Rangers at the Abubakar Tafawa Balewa Stadium, as they seek for their first win in the season of the abridged league.